<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Ceanothus velutinus </i>sprouts vigorously from the root crown if top-killed or cut. Seeds readily germinate after fire or other disturbance (Anderson 2001b, Francis 2002a).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (40-75 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Seasonality</td>
			<td>Summer-early fall
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
